  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;My stay in ward D5 in August 2019&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Kenneth Ibbotson&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;In July 2019 I was admitted to Stepping Hill and had an abscess removed from my back passage. On returning home and being attended by district nurses my condition worsened and I was re admitted this time to ward d5. I was diagnosed as having a fissure adjacent to my back passage and the only way to give it sufficient space to heal I would have to undergo a COLOSTOMY. Four times I was put on 'nil by mouth' waiting for surgery and four times (thank goodness )I was taken back to the ward because of more pressing emergencies.
During this waiting period I was being monitored by the ward staff and an ANGEL out of the Pharmacy department spotted an anomaly in my medication. I was taking a tablet prescribed previously by the Cardiology dept. called Nicorandil  which has a proven record of viciously attacking fissures etc. After some discussion among the Consultants it was decided to change my medication and within a few days I noticed a definite improvement to my problem.
My wife and I brought this to the notice of the Consultants and again after discussions, the surgery was cancelled and  I was allowed to go home.5 weeks later I attended the same Consultant and was discharged.
My wife and I will be forever grateful for the diligence and dedication of the young lady in the pharmacy department.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
